Ralph P. Scozzafava  CEO & Director, Dean Foods CompanyAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships58$3,934,537As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Ralph P. Scozzafava has been the Chief Executive Officer of Dean Foods Company since January 1, 2017. Mr. Scozzafava served as the Chief Operating Officer and Executive Vice President at Dean Foods Company since October 1, 2015 and October 13, 2014 respectively until January 1, 2017. He served as the Chief Commercial Officer at Dean Foods Company since October 13, 2014 until October 1, 2015. He served as the Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer at FBI ... Wind Down, Inc. from May 1, 2008 to November 2013 and January 1, 2008 to November 2013 respectively. Mr. Scozzafava served as Vice President of Worldwide Commercial Operations at Wm. Wrigley Jr. Company from March 1, 2006 to February 2007. He served as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Furniture Brands International since April 2009. He served at Campbell Soup Company from 1996 to 2000, where he served various senior executive level positions. He began his professional career in 1982 at Warner Lambert. He served as Vice President and Managing Director for North America/Pacific of Wm. Wrigley Jr. Company since 2004. He served as Vice President and General Manager for U.S. of Wm. Wrigley Jr. Company from 2002 to 2003 and served as Vice President, U.S. Sales and Customer Marketing from 2001 to 2002. He served as Vice President of Wm. Wrigley Jr. Company and was responsible for its North America Group and the Pacific Region. He joined Wrigley Wm Jr. Co. in 2000 and served until 2007, where he was responsible for the sales, marketing, finance and people, Learning and Development Functions for the U.S. business. He served various executive positions with the Campbell's Soup Company for five years prior to joining William Wrigley Jr. Co. Mr. Scozzafava serves as Chairman of the Board for Keep America Beautiful Inc. Mr. Scozzafava served as the Chairman of the Board at American Home Furnishings Alliance, Inc. from January 1, 2012 to December 31, 2012. He serves as a Director of Boston-based Center on Media and Child Health and Chicago-based Heartland Alliance. He served as Vice Chairman of FBI Wind Down, Inc. from June 2007 to April 2008. He has been a Director of Dean Foods Company since January 1, 2017. Mr. Scozzafava has been an Independent Director at American Home Furnishings Alliance, Inc., since January 2010. Mr. Scozzafava served as an Independent  Director of Stage Stores, Inc. from February 21, 2012 to June 01, 2017. He served as a Director at FBI Wind Down, Inc. from June 2007 to November 2013.Read Full Background




