Mr. Ralph P. Scozzafava served as the Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer at FBI Wind Down, Inc. from May 1, 2008 to November 2013 and January 1, 2008 to November 2013 respectively. Mr. Scozzafava served as Vice President of Worldwide Commercial Operations at Wm. Wrigley Jr. Company from March 1, 2006 to February 2007. He served at Campbell Soup Company from 1996 to 2000, where he served various senior executive level positions. Mr. Scozzafava began his professional career in 1982 at Warner Lambert. He served as Vice President and Managing Director for North America/Pacific of Wm. Wrigley Jr. Company since 2004. He served as Vice President and General Manager for U.S. of Wm. Wrigley Jr. Company from 2002 to 2003 and served as Vice President, U.S. Sales and Customer Marketing from 2001 to 2002. He served as Vice President of Wm. Wrigley Jr. Company and was responsible for its North America Group and the Pacific Region. Mr. Scozzafava joined Wrigley Wm Jr. Co. in 2000 and served until 2007, where he was responsible for the sales, marketing, finance and people, Learning and Development Functions for the U.S. business. He served various executive positions with the Campbell’s Soup Company for five years prior to joining William Wrigley Jr. Co. Mr. Scozzafava serves as Chairman of the Board for Keep America Beautiful Inc. Mr. Scozzafava served as the Chairman of the Board at American Home Furnishings Alliance, Inc. from January 1, 2012 to December 31, 2012. He serves as a Director of Boston-based Center on Media and Child Health and Chicago-based Heartland Alliance. He served as Vice Chairman of FBI Wind Down, Inc. from June 2007 to April 2008. Mr. Scozzafava has been a Director of Stage Stores Inc since February 21, 2012 and American Home Furnishings Alliance, Inc., since January 2010. He served as a Director of FBI Wind Down, Inc. from June 2007 to November 2013.



